[{"id":"1776531526508","ulid":"01KPGRFMWBJRM7AYVYKRTXH3J4","ts":1776552625442,"task":"Our project is to determine compatability with people based off their instagram activity (eg posts, reels, comments, etc). The interface should be between two people where there is a middle man that takes their data and gives them back a compatability score and a list of things they have in common. The point of this is to help break the ice without sharing things they dont have in common and to prevent oversharing. You have direction over every abstraction level and level in the software stack. How do we go about this?","tokensIn":771,"tokensOut":94460,"cacheWrites":872303,"cacheReads":6495485,"totalCost":11.064991250000004,"size":2168956,"cwdOnTaskInitialization":"/home/mhassoun/hackmsa","conversationHistoryDeletedRange":[2,99],"isFavorited":false,"modelId":"claude-opus-4-5-20251101"},{"id":"1776536264549","ulid":"01KPGX07VBJDT5JMRBMDKDCF5A","ts":1776536313746,"task":"mhassoun@xcomhassoun50x-18% cat /etc/os-release \nNAME=\"Red Hat Enterprise Linux\"\nVERSION=\"8.10 (Ootpa)\"\nID=\"rhel\"\nID_LIKE=\"fedora\"\nVERSION_ID=\"8.10\"\nPLATFORM_ID=\"platform:el8\"\nPRETTY_NAME=\"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8.10 (Ootpa)\"\nANSI_COLOR=\"0;31\"\nCPE_NAME=\"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:8::baseos\"\nHOME_URL=\"https://www.redhat.com/\"\nDOCUMENTATION_URL=\"https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_enterprise_linux/8\"\nBUG_REPORT_URL=\"https://bugzilla.redhat.com/\"\n\nREDHAT_BUGZILLA_PRODUCT=\"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8\"\nREDHAT_BUGZILLA_PRODUCT_VERSION=8.10\nREDHAT_SUPPORT_PRODUCT=\"Red Hat Enterprise Linux\"\nREDHAT_SUPPORT_PRODUCT_VERSION=\"8.10\"\nmhassoun@xcomhassoun50x-19% pip3 install -r requirements.txt\nCollecting fastapi==0.109.0 (from -r requirements.txt (line 4))\n  Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement fastapi==0.109.0 (from -r requirements.txt (line 4)) (from versions: 0.1.0, 0.1.2, 0.1.3, 0.1.4, 0.1.5, 0.1.6, 0.1.7, 0.1.8, 0.1.9, 0.1.10, 0.1.11, 